<!-- ============ SECTION 1: THE FULL LIFECYCLE ============ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-row">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="section-eyebrow">Full-Lifecycle RFID</span>
        <h2>Every unit gets a license plate. Every movement <span class="gradient-text">tracked.</span></h2>
        <p>Each tag carries an Electronic Product Code (EPC) — the UPC plus a unique serial number. That means 10 units of the same SKU are 10 individually identifiable items, not a count of "10." This distinction is fundamental: it's why our stock counts are accurate and why our loss prevention actually works.</p>
        <ul class="feature-bullets">
          <li>Source tagging: integrate with manufacturers to commission EPCs at the point of creation</li>
          <li>In-transit visibility: see RFID-tagged containers on the water, in customs, arriving at the dock</li>
          <li>Receiving and commissioning: tag, encode, and scan inbound shipments in one step via the purchase receipt workflow — low-power mode prevents reading surrounding inventory</li>
          <li>Unit control ledger: full transactional history for every EPC — where it was received, counted, transferred, sold, and whitelisted</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Book a demo <i class="ti ti-arrow-right"></i></a>
