<!-- ============ SECTION 2: SMART READING — POWER MODES ============ -->
<section class="section" style="padding-top: 0;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-row reverse">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="section-eyebrow">Intelligent Reading</span>
        <h2>Smart enough to know what it <span class="gradient-text">should</span> read.</h2>
        <p>Different workflows need different RFID behavior. Receiving stock requires tight, low-power reading so you only capture what's directly in front of you — not the 500 items on the racks behind you. Stock counting needs the opposite: maximum range to sweep an entire store in minutes. Our system adapts automatically.</p>
        <ul class="feature-bullets">
          <li>Low-power mode for transactions: receiving, transfers, selling — reads only items within inches of the device</li>
          <li>High-power mode for counting: full-store sweeps that capture thousands of EPCs in minutes</li>
          <li>Confirmation logic: a tag must be read consistently (multiple reads per second) before it's counted — no phantom reads from items passing by</li>
          <li>Anti-bleed technology: tags respond only to the specific antenna that energized them, preventing cross-contamination between checkout zones</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <!-- Mockup: Power mode comparison -->
      <div class="feature-visual">
